    "details": {
      "blurb": "Brotherhood shadowcount; would-be curate",
      "languages": {
        "details": "",
        "value": [
          "common",
          "infernal",
          "shadowtongue"
        ]
      },
      "level": {
        "value": 12
      },
      "privateNotes": "",
      "publicNotes": "<p><strong>Role:</strong> Brotherhood of Bones shadowcount — Laori's partner, polished where she is chipper, patient where she is gleeful (they genuinely dislike each other; @Check[type:perception|dc:20] reads his frustration with her). The Brotherhood's goal is real — <em>capture the Crown of Fangs, gather every Kazavon relic, ensure the champion is never resurrected</em> — but the pair have been feeding <strong>false reports to Nidal for months</strong> to keep the glory for themselves; no true Kuthite can even carry Serithtial, so they need the PCs. <strong>Run the Devil-You-Know mechanic</strong> (Background page): whichever agent the PCs trust becomes the <em>Ally</em> (loyal, shares lore, effectively auto-succeeds the chapter's Scarwall-history checks); the other becomes the <em>Enemy</em> — quietly jealous, prone to 'accidentally' catching PCs in spell areas, and destined to turn at the Star Tower (G7), where the Enemy demands the Ally atone by taking the curacy. If the post falls to him in the end, Sial relents and accepts — gone to the Plane of Shadow.</p>",
      "publication": {
        "title": "Pathfinder: Curse of the Crimson Throne (PF2e conversion, private)",
        "authors": "",
        "license": "OGL",
        "remaster": true
      }
